    "last_activity_date" : 1473196812,
    "creation_date" : 1473196812,
    "answer_id" : 39358015,
    "question_id" : 30130180,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For Windows 7 this JVM argument worked for me (Java 8u102) and is necessary to auto scale with all dpi settings. The minimal setting to activate Hi DPI is set to 1 (100%). Without this setting the 125% dpi setting in Windows 7 will not auto-scale, while 150% and 200% will:</p>\n\n<pre><code>-Dglass.win.minHiDPI=1\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In an JavaFX <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/deploy/packaging.html#A1321122\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ant deploy</a> the above setting can be applied like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;fx:deploy\n   &lt;fx:platform javafx=\"2.1+\"&gt;\n       &lt;fx:property name=\"glass.win.minHiDPI\" value=\"1\"/&gt;\n   &lt;/fx:platform&gt;\n&lt;/fx:deploy&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26739540,
      "reputation" : 580,
      "user_id" : 20340543,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/391fa27c030df060dd7293769457b56c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
